The `--max-retries` flag controls the number of times Nmap will retry a scan request if it times out or receives an error. 

Setting a low `--max-retries` value (e.g., 1 or 2) can make the scan appear less persistent and reduce the chances of triggering an alert. However, it may also result in missing some valid responses, so it's a trade-off.

